Defence PS Kirimi Kaberia has said the government will do everything possible to ensure relief food is distributed to all starving Kenyans in time to save lives.Speaking at Mutuati Catholic Church in Igembe North constituency while distributing food on Saturday, he said the government has already identified the regions worst-hit by the drought.&ldquo;We know many people countrywide have been affected by drought, but I want to assure you no single Kenyan will die of starvation. The government has put in place measures to ensure those affected get relief food in time,&rdquo; Kaberia said.He urged those distributing relief food not to divert it to undeserving people.Mount Kenya Foundation national chairman Mutuma Nkanata urged Kenyans to register as voters before the Tuesday deadline.